WEBVTT

00:00.568 --> 00:02.202
<i>In New York
city's war on crime,</i>

00:02.203 --> 00:05.271
<i>the worst criminal offenders
are pursued</i>

00:05.272 --> 00:07.574
<i>by the detectives
of the Major Case Squad.</i>

00:07.575 --> 00:09.543
<i>These are their stories.</i>

00:12.646 --> 00:16.149
I'm going to connect
the robotic arm to the trocar.

00:16.149 --> 00:18.918
We can start our
robotic prostate surgery.

00:18.919 --> 00:21.121
Bloodless surgery
without scalpel.

00:21.122 --> 00:23.456
- The surgeon controls
the robotic arm

00:23.457 --> 00:25.658
from the console
guided by video.

00:25.659 --> 00:27.327
- Wow, that's amazing.

00:27.328 --> 00:29.295
Surgery of the future,
and it's here now.

00:29.296 --> 00:31.097
- Thanks to your generosity.

00:31.098 --> 00:32.598
Speaking of which,

00:32.600 --> 00:34.200
any hints
on who will receive

00:34.201 --> 00:35.635
this year's Langston grant?

00:35.636 --> 00:38.037
- I'll announce
at the dedication.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.939
- We're all
on pins and needles.

00:39.940 --> 00:41.508
Till tonight.

00:41.509 --> 00:43.676
- So do you think I could
take this thing for a spin?

00:43.677 --> 00:45.011
Looks like a lot of fun.

00:45.012 --> 00:47.647
- Why not?
The patient's already dead.

00:55.556 --> 00:58.158
- Did you read
my amended proposal

00:58.159 --> 00:59.626
on spinal cord regeneration?

00:59.627 --> 01:01.427
- Uh, I did.

01:01.428 --> 01:04.197
- Imagine a world
without wheelchairs,

01:04.197 --> 01:06.966
wounded soldiers
walking again.

01:06.967 --> 01:09.469
The military contract alone
will be worth a fortune.

01:09.470 --> 01:10.937
- It's not about money.

01:10.938 --> 01:12.939
- Says the man
with all the money.

01:15.910 --> 01:17.777
- I see you still
like to make jokes.

01:21.715 --> 01:24.284
- Langston played it
close to the vest.

01:24.285 --> 01:26.119
Any of us could be
the winner tonight.

01:26.120 --> 01:27.787
- Nice for you,
giving him the tour.

01:27.788 --> 01:29.255
Last chance to self-promote.

01:29.256 --> 01:31.024
- Don't worry,
he still hates me.

01:31.025 --> 01:32.725
- You ask me,
Langston's a wannabe.

01:32.726 --> 01:36.162
- Who personally controls
a $20 million research grant.

01:36.163 --> 01:38.731
- Look, he flunked
out of bedford.

01:38.732 --> 01:40.466
He made his fortune
developing a pill coating.

01:40.467 --> 01:41.601
He's a pharmacist.

01:41.602 --> 01:43.403
I don't even
want to go tonight.

01:43.404 --> 01:44.938
- How bad can it be?

01:44.939 --> 01:46.339
Cheese cubes, bad wine,

01:46.340 --> 01:47.373
and we can bring a date.

01:47.374 --> 01:48.808
How 'bout it,
you and me?

01:48.809 --> 01:51.911
- Sorry,
I'm taking my mom.

01:51.912 --> 01:53.947
- You really are
the good girl.

01:53.948 --> 01:56.416
- You should see
these surgical robots, boy.

01:56.417 --> 01:59.185
Tiny cameras
on the instruments.

01:59.186 --> 02:02.589
Like you're actually
inside the human body.

02:02.590 --> 02:03.856
- Fascinating.

02:06.527 --> 02:08.627
That's a nice shirt.
- Yeah?

02:08.628 --> 02:10.128
- Mm-hmm,
I like it.

02:10.130 --> 02:12.298
- Hmm.

02:12.299 --> 02:14.867
You know, I was thinking
I might drive.

02:14.868 --> 02:17.270
Or do you want
to take a limo?

02:17.271 --> 02:18.938
- Why don't you take the car?

02:18.939 --> 02:20.974
I might have to duck out.
I feel a migraine coming on.

02:20.975 --> 02:22.709
- Okay.

02:28.782 --> 02:30.683
Ah.

02:30.684 --> 02:32.118
- Look, daddy, it's you
fighting a dragon.

02:32.119 --> 02:33.987
- Oh, yeah, it looks
just like me too.

02:33.988 --> 02:35.255
You got the horns,
you got the wings,

02:35.256 --> 02:37.457
you got the-
that's the dragon!

02:40.494 --> 02:41.894
- Get going.

02:41.895 --> 02:43.896
And I'm honored
to be here tonight

02:43.897 --> 02:46.532
as head of Langston
pharmaceuticals

02:46.533 --> 02:50.236
to dedicate the Da Vinci
surgical training suite.

02:52.773 --> 02:55.174
And I'm proud to support
our next generation

02:55.175 --> 02:56.509
of researchers,

02:56.510 --> 02:58.177
the best and the brightest.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.946
You young doctors,

02:59.947 --> 03:02.315
who one day
will wipe out disease

03:02.316 --> 03:04.984
and eradicate suffering.

03:08.455 --> 03:12.158
So drum roll please.

03:12.159 --> 03:14.460
It's time to announce
this year's winner

03:14.461 --> 03:16.629
of the Langston
research grant.

03:19.466 --> 03:21.200
Dr. Maya zhuang.

03:24.004 --> 03:26.005
For her work
on creating a vaccine

03:26.006 --> 03:29.375
to help cure
childhood leukemia.

03:29.376 --> 03:32.445
Congratulations,
Dr. zhuang.

03:40.821 --> 03:42.689
- I alady thanked Langston.

03:42.690 --> 03:44.023
- Okay, thank him again.

03:44.024 --> 03:45.858
It's a big honor.

03:45.859 --> 03:48.261
Oh, Maya,
I'm so proud of you.

03:48.262 --> 03:50.563
- Don't try and charm me.
I'm not an idiot, all right?

03:50.564 --> 03:53.499
I know that you pour money
into the institution.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.368
You think that it's gonna
save everything, okay?

03:55.369 --> 03:57.003
No, I don't want
anything from you.

03:57.004 --> 03:58.671
So stay away from me.

03:58.672 --> 04:00.740
Stay away from me,
all right?

04:00.741 --> 04:02.208
- This isn't a good time.
- Shh.

04:02.209 --> 04:03.810
- And you're a phony,
and you're a son of a bitch!

04:03.811 --> 04:06.813
All right?

04:10.984 --> 04:12.652
- Stella, what are you
still doing awake?

04:12.653 --> 04:14.253
- Where's daddy?

04:14.254 --> 04:17.123
- He must still be
at the party.

04:17.124 --> 04:20.993
- I've been calling him.
He won't pick up.

04:20.994 --> 04:22.862
Why are you home so late?

04:22.863 --> 04:24.864
- Uh, get her to bed,
florelle.

04:24.865 --> 04:27.500
- Yes, Mrs. Langston.

04:27.501 --> 04:29.736
- Night-night, Stella.

